.TH BUDYK 8 "2026-04-22" "budyk 0.2.0"
.SH NAME
budyk \- lightweight server monitoring with adaptive collection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B budyk
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B serve
Start the monitoring daemon and web server.
.TP
.B tui
Start the terminal UI.
.TP
.B hash\-password
Generate an Argon2id password hash for web authentication.
.TP
.B suggest\-rules
Generate monitoring rule suggestions from collected history.
.TP
.B version
Print version and exit.
.SH DESCRIPTION
budyk is a self-contained server monitoring daemon. It collects system
metrics using an adaptive 3-level model (heartbeat / watchful / active),
stores them in tiered ring-buffer files, and serves them via a real-time
web dashboard and terminal TUI.
.PP
Monitoring rules are written in Lua and evaluated on each collection tick.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/etc/budyk/config.yaml
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/local/etc/budyk/rules.lua
Lua monitoring rules.
.TP
.I /var/db/budyk/
Ring-buffer data directory.
.SH LICENSE
BSD-3-Clause
